ial beneficial effects in academic proficiency across languages in migrant children.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCode switching (Linguistics) 0aCode switching (Linguistics). 0aEducation, Bilingual. 0aHeritage language speakersxEducation. 0aImmigrant childrenxEducation. 0aInterlanguage (Language learning) 0aInterlanguage (Language learning). 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aMultilingual education. 0aMultilingualism in children. 0aSociolinguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aSLA.  abilingual education.  abilingualism.  abiliteracy.  acrosslinguistic influence.  aheritage language learning.  aheritage language maintenance.  aheritage language students.  aheritage language.  ainterdependence.  alinguistic transfer.  aliteracy development.  aliteracy skills.  aliteracy.  amultilingual language development.  amultilingualism.  asecond language acquisition.  atransfer.1 aBayer, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerthele, Raphael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerthele, Raphael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDesgrippes, Magalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrompàk, Edina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLambelet, Amelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLambelet, Amelia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoser, Urs, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNieminen, Lea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPestana, Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTomasi